messages: 1	1	1	2026	I had a couple of shadowing shifts in December which seemed to have gone well. We were able to discover a way to do cleaning without breaking the systen or canceling any rounds which is great.

Most of my focus this month was more on my first solo BUSM shifts. Nothing out of the ordinary happened during the shifts and overall i would call them successful but i definetly noticed that compared some of the more experienced SM's since i do things a bit more slowly i have a bit of a hard time paying attention to everything that is happening in the studio at the same time as i'm supposed to fill SM obligations. I hope next month will be even more successful and i'll be able to get even more experience in this new role.	Reduce errors - Still busy
Making sure everyone is using correct operational programs, Google - Complete
Integrating to Google - complete	Errors did reduce a bit but fortunately they are not increasing compared to some previous months.
A lot of my team members took extra shifts this month which i'm very happy about.

Unfortunately some of the members were involved in the misbehaviors that should not be happening.
